_url":"https://github.com/amholler","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amholler/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-06-17T17:04:20Z","updated_at":"2022-06-17T17:04:20Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"TL;DR:\r\n For tabular & text classification datasets used in AutoML development, 3 simultaneous trials each using 1 T4 GPU, worked well.\r\n For tabular datasets, hyperparameter search time budgets of 2 hrs were standard.\r\n For text classification datasets, hyperparameter search time budgets were varied with dataset width, since Bert is quadratic.\r\n\r\nDetails on AutoML development and validation, including dataset sizes and other aspects of the workloads, are here:\r\n Tabular AutoML: https://medium.com/predibase/ludwig-automl-for-deep-learning-cf64de9d49c8\r\n Text Classification AutoML: https://medium.com/predibase/ludwig-automl-for-text-classification-7c1759f3b150\r\n\r\nDetails on how the resource configuration worked for Tabular AutoML, including trial node usage over time, are here:\r\n https://www.cncf.io/blog/2022/02/15/managing-public-cloud-resources-for-deep-learning-training-experiments-and-lessons-learned/","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ludwig-ai/ludwig/issues/comments/1159073732/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"